> Sweeter and thicker than soy sauce, ketjap manis is typically used in Indonesian cuisine. This condiment is a staple in our Asian style recipes and you can find it in anything from larb style salads to fried rice and noodle dishes.

== Vegetables and Noodles ==

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length
of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}
(or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} and cook until
tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

== Plant-Based Mince ==

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} to the pan.

Use a #spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks. Cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Once the plant-based mince is cooked, transfer it to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Veggies ==

Wipe out your (now empty) #frying pan{} and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle
of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add the carrot
ribbons and garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds} more.

Add a splash of @water{}, then cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to cook
until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Honey Sesame Sauce and Assembly ==

While the veg cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @Soy Sauce{25%ml},
@Ketjap Manis{50%g}, @Honey{15%g}, @Tomato Ketchup{1.5%tbsp} and
@Water for the Sauce{50%ml} with half the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the veg is cooked, add the cooked mince and noodles to the pan.

Pour in the sticky sauce and stir together until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, share the honey sesame veggie mince noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining sesame seeds to finish for those who'd like them.

Enjoy!